3 Real World Applications: 

1. Social Media - Database used: NoSQL
Social Media stores billions of posts, comments, users and their activities. NoSQL databases can scale horizontally and handle large volumes of unstructured data.

2. Banking System - Database used: SQL
Banking systems require strong consistency, ACID transactions and structured data consisting of user accounts, bank balances and transactions. SQL databases help ensure data integrity and prevent partial or duplicate transactions.

3. Redis - Database used: In-memory
Frequently accessed data are stored in-memory databases for fast access and reduce latency.
